<br>
In space, not having to come back makes the task enormously easier since a fueled return vehicle does not have to be taken along. This exponentially reduces the complexity and the total mass requirement. Offsetting this to some extent is the need to take along an enormously comprehensive array of equipment and supplies, everything needed in fact to set up a viable community. This would not have to be fully self-sustaining at first, since one way resupply flights would be relatively simple. Very early flights would probably have to be round-trip to provide the data and experience needed for planning a large scale colonization flight. The latter would not be permanently marooned, of course, since part of its equipment would be machinery for producing propellant for eventual 2-way traffic.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=philfossil>philfossil</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/28/03 7:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=601.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pioneering Mars, one way trip</span><hr size=1> Yes one way trip is very logical but remember that most of the one way trips to america resulted in &quot;lost colonies&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/28/03 8:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=601.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pioneering Mars, one way trip</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yes one way trip is very logical but remember that most of the one way trips to america resulted in &quot;lost colonies&quot;.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
