for people to grow food and live off the land on Mars in general.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 1/29/03 6:46:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orion Commander</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/29/03 7:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=601.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: settlers vs explorers</span><hr size=1> like i said before-maybe 1 or 2 from each 4 person crew could stay for an extra rotation or two.  if enough people stayed for 2 rotations, much more science could be done, and more physical work.  eventually, people could stay for 4 or 5 rotations.   we should absolutely give the option to return, but we should encourage crew memebers to stay....possibly having two slots for mandatory return, 2 for voluntary return on the crew membership.<br>
<br>
this would allow us to keep larger numbers of people on the mission, and still return the science data. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tmayes1999>tmayes1999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/30/03 6:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=601.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: settlers vs explorers</span><hr size=1> How about this approach.<br>
We launch D-100 class  20 ton  ships to mars on a 1 way journey. Each ship carries one highly technologicaly, and scientificly literate married couple. Each ship would be driven<br>
by any of the following propulsion sysems, a bimodal Ntr-Nep<br>
engine   or solar sail/ solar electric  + h2 +o2 chemical rocket combination.The carrier  vehicle to put the d-100 in leo<br>
 could any of the following:<br>
1. U.S Titian 3 or Titian 4  booster <br>
2. French Ariane booster<br>
3. Russian proton booster<br>
4. Japanese h-2 booster.<br>
5.Chinese long march 4 or 5 booster.<br>
6. Or my personal designs which are 1. an H2 + O2<br>
burning two stage Trojan 2 or Trojan  3  medium lift booster<br>
Trojan 3 is comparable to Titian 4 in lifting power.<br>
Trojan 4 is comparable to Energia or Saturn 5 in lifting<br>
 power  <br>
